Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and chop @yellow onion{1}. Peel @carrot{1}, then halve lengthwise. Slice into thin half-moons. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

Combine @ground pork{16%ounce}, half @ricotta cheese{4%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @salt{1/4%tsp}, half the garlic, and half the @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon} in a large #bowl{}. Gently mix just until blended.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a medium #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion, carrot, remaining garlic, remaining Italian seasoning, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add @water{8%cups} and @chicken stock concentrate{4}. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and let simmer.

While soup simmers, form meatballs: shape meatball mix into round balls (use about a heaping TBSP for each). Repeat until all of mixture is used.

> TIP: Be gentle with the meat—overworking it will cause the meatballs to lose their fluffiness.

Stir @Israeli couscous{1%cup} into soup, then carefully drop in meatballs. Return to a simmer and cook until meatballs are no longer pink on outside, about ~{3%minutes}. Add @kale{8%ounce}. Cook until leaves are tender and couscous is al dente, about ~{4%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Ladle soup into #bowls{}. Sprinkle @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} over each bowl and serve.